When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

When you don't probably have enough space on your local computer or if you want to collaborate with a remote team who should also be able to access your files

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
In case of collaboration with different teams, it might be first useful to view the commits made there by other team members and CHOOSE
to pull only those changes that are useful. Manual pull is useful in such cases 

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

Forks are for edits on the Github platform. To be used without disturbing another persons , but using it as a starting point
Clones are copies. To copy on to ones computer from Github.  
Branches are experimental paths used for trying out new features
